{
  "id": "n27Dv4dN",
  "name": "Equations",
  "intro": [
    "<p>So far we've mostly built terms affecting their arguments",
    "in a uniform way. But what about distinguishing arguments?</p>",
    "<p>The trick is almost always to put some unknowns to the argument,",
    "add some extra probe arguments to both sides, and try to achieve a simpler equation.</p>",
    "<p>Throughout this chapter, producing an equivalent term",
    "(given enough extra arguments) is enough.</p>"
  ],
  "content": [
    {
      "id": "3YiOt9K9",
      "created_at": "2026-07-16T20:23:34Z",
      "name": "Warm up",
      "intro": [
        "<p>Create a term that returns <code>K</code> for <code>I</code>",
        "and <code>I</code> for <code>K</code>.</p>"
      ],
      "input": { "name": "phi", "fancy": "&phi;" },
      "cases": [
        ["phi K x", "x"],
        ["phi I x y", "x"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5SupNbQO",
      "created_at": "2026-07-16T20:46:42Z",
      "name": "Identity upgrade",
      "intro": [
        "<p>Create a term that converts <code>I</code> to <code>K</code>,",
        "and leaves <code>KI</code> in place.</p>",
        "<p>What it does to other terms is irrelevant. Multiple solutions exist.</p>"
      ],
      "input": { "name": "phi", "fancy": "&phi;" },
      "cases": [
        ["phi I x y", "x"],
        ["phi (KI) x y", "y"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tY6UuNQ6",
      "created_at": "2026-07-16T21:26:17Z",
      "name": "vice-",
      "intro": [
        "<p>Create term <code>f</code> such that",
        "<code>f I = S</code>, <code>f S = K</code>, and <code>f K = I</code>.</p>"
      ],
      "input": "f",
      "cases": [
        ["f I x y z", "x z (y z)"],
        ["f S x y", "x"],
        ["f K x", "x"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "NUDTbx2N",
      "created_at": "2026-07-16T21:26:17Z",
      "name": "-versa",
      "intro": [
        "<p>Create term <code>f</code> such that",
        "<code>f S = I</code>, <code>f I = K</code>, and <code>f K = S</code>.</p>",
        "<p>This and previous puzzle names were shamelessly stolen from",
        "the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supaplex\" target=\"_blank\">Supaplex</a> game.</p>"
      ],
      "input": "f",
      "cases": [
        ["f K x y z", "x z (y z)"],
        ["f I x y", "x"],
        ["f S x", "x"]
      ]
    }
  ]
}
